# Dark theme only

FlowDesk does **not** ship a light theme. Treat the app as **dark-only** unless the user explicitly asks otherwise.

## Do

- Use existing tokens from `styles.css`: `var(--bg-primary)`, `var(--bg-card)`, `var(--text-primary)`, `var(--text-secondary)`, `var(--border)`, `var(--purple)`, etc.
- Style new UI (forms, modals, tables, dropdowns) to match current auth/dashboard patterns: dark surfaces, readable contrast, muted secondary text.
- For native controls (`select`, inputs), keep **`color-scheme: dark`** where appropriate and explicit **`option` / focus** colors so OS dropdown lists stay readable on Windows/Chrome.
- Prefer shared classes (e.g. `form-input`, `form-select`, `btn-submit`) over one-off light backgrounds.

## Don’t

- Add light/dark **theme toggles**, `prefers-color-scheme` branching, or a second palette “for light mode.”
- Use white or near-white **page backgrounds** or **large light panels** that break the dark aesthetic.
- Rely on browser default form colors without checking contrast on dark backgrounds.

If a third-party component defaults to light styling, override it to match the dark tokens above.
